              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/essay/my-alma-mater-auschwitz-edith-bruck" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Bruck-anchor.jpg?itok=DYlohAe3" width="250" height="175" alt="A photograph of a lit candle emerging from the darkness. Text reads: International Holocaust Remebrance Day: Jan. 27, 2025" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/essay/my-alma-mater-auschwitz-edith-bruck">My Alma Mater Is Auschwitz</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/edith-bruck" hreflang="en">Edith Bruck</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/essay/language-white-bones-secrets-han-kangs-poetic-prose-eun-gwi-chung" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Chung-A.jpg?itok=4cUAaNkT" width="250" height="175" alt="A black and white photograph of Han Kang" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/essay/language-white-bones-secrets-han-kangs-poetic-prose-eun-gwi-chung">Language of White Bones: The Secrets of Han Kang’s Poetic Prose</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/eun-gwi-chung" hreflang="en">Eun-Gwi Chung</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/essay/street-kiss-feng-jicai" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/FengKiss-w.jpg?itok=ygj3q-NA" width="250" height="175" alt="A black and white photograph of a man and a woman kissing in on a busy city street" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

